The paper deals with the automatic extraction of data from Wiktionary, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as parsing and semantic analysis. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also describes the storage of the extracted data in a relational database schema, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for disambiguation and classification, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the release of the parser software under an open source license, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
